	libmedio is a comprehensive C++ oriented fully portable shared library
which provides direct IO classes to access and generate different types of
data/image files which are commonly used by medical applications.

  It should server modern C++ oriented applications with an easy API to 
data formats like ECAT6/7, MicroPET, Interfile and other data container
formats. It is fully written in C++ using the QT framework of Trolltech
(www.trolltech.com) to ensure portability across many different operating
systems.

  As the main routines has been first developed for an application used
in PET (Positron Emission Tomography), it mainly focuses on support for
ECAT6 and 7 files, but should also be the favourite library for accessing
and converting the data of formats like Interfile and MicroPET specific
data streams. 

Requirements:
------------
	As the library's intention is to be used in C++ application, you require
a modern C++ compiler, preferable GCC in its 3.4+ version. And as the
library is written using QT you require at least version 3 of the QT
framework for the platform you want to compile the library for.

Features:
--------

- full ECAT7 sinogram read/write support.
- full object oriented design and implementation using C++ and QT.
- highly portable implementation with direct implementations existing for
	SunOS, MacOSX and Linux. (more to come)
- Doxygen based class documentation and a deeper implementation 
	documentation based on the MSc thesis of my computer science study.
- Released under LGPL (Lesser General Public License) for a maximum
	available flexibility and developer support aswell as the possibility to
	use the library in commercial applications.

Future plans:
